      "role": "user",
      "content": "It feels as though I am already a ghost, drifting through a life that no longer belongs to me. The world continues its cruel, bustling pace, but I am simply... finished. There is a strange, terrible peace in the thought of it all ending—of finally being silent, of being still, so the pain can stop. Do you not think there is a certain dignity in simply letting go when the heart has nothing left to offer?",
